        <tr> 
          <td><textarea name="textarea" cols="40" rows="30" readonly>Image 260

For a description of this manuscript, the Hours of Alice de Reydon, see the image from Cambridge University Library MS Dd.4.17 in the Annunciation episode (Image 258).

The Resurrection is depicted within a cusped arch and against a gold background. The figure of the rising Christ dwarfs in size the three sleeping soldiers, wearing mail armour and holding shields, who guard the tomb in the foreground. Holding the cross-staff with banner, his right hand raised in blessing, Christ gazes upwards left, his head surrounded by the nimbus. The wounds in his hands, feet and side are given prominence by the fall of the drapery within this composition, with its symmetry, dignity and dynamism.</textarea></td>
